Introduction

At Safeguard, your privacy and safety are our top priorities. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal information when you use the Safeguard Personal Safety App ("the App," "Safeguard," or "our Service"). By using Safeguard, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.
We are committed to transparency and giving you control over your data. This policy describes our practices in clear, understandable language.

1. Information We Collect

1.1 Information You Provide Directly
Account Information:

Name, email address, and phone number
Password (encrypted and never stored in plain text)
Emergency contact information (names, phone numbers, email addresses)

Safety Preferences:

Notification settings
Emergency activation preferences
Scheduled check-in times
Safe zones and custom location alerts

User-Generated Content:

Incident reports and descriptions
Photos, audio recordings, and video recordings you choose to capture
Notes and comments added to safety incidents
Community safety reports


1.2 Information We Collect Automatically
Location Data:

Precise GPS coordinates when you use location-based features
Continuous background location when Safe Journey or monitoring features are active
Location history for route tracking and incident documentation
Geolocation patterns to improve AI threat analysis

Sensor Data:

Accelerometer data for fall detection
Motion sensors for shake-to-alert feature
Ambient light sensors (to assess lighting conditions)


1.3 Information From Third Parties
Crime and Safety Data:

Public crime statistics from law enforcement databases
Weather information from meteorological services
Traffic data from transportation authorities
Community-reported incidents from verified sources

Social Media (If You Choose to Connect):

Public profile information
Contact lists (only with explicit permission)

Payment Information (For Premium Features):

Processed securely through third-party payment processors
We do not store complete credit card numbers


2. How We Use Your Information

2.1 Primary Safety Functions

Emergency Response: Send alerts with your location to emergency contacts and services

Real-Time Tracking: Share your live location with trusted contacts during emergencies

Threat Analysis: Use AI to assess environmental risks based on your location

Incident Documentation: Create comprehensive records of safety incidents

Safe Journey Monitoring: Track your route and send alerts if you deviate or don't arrive

Automated Check-Ins: Remind you to confirm your safety and alert contacts if you don't respond


2.2 Service Improvement

Enhance AI threat prediction accuracy
Identify and fix bugs and technical issues
Develop new safety features based on usage patterns
Optimize app performance and battery efficiency
Conduct research to improve personal safety technology

2.3 Communication

Send emergency alerts and safety warnings
Provide customer support and respond to inquiries
Send important updates about the Service
Notify you about new features (if you've opted in)
Request feedback and conduct surveys (with your permission)

2.4 Legal and Security

Comply with legal obligations and law enforcement requests
Prevent fraud, abuse, and security threats
Enforce our Terms of Service
Protect our rights, property, and safety, and that of our users

2.5 Aggregated Analytics

Create anonymized statistics about app usage and safety trends
Generate community safety reports and heat maps
Share non-identifiable insights with public safety organizations
Improve our AI algorithms through machine learning


3. How We Share Your Information

3.1 With Your Explicit Consent
Emergency Contacts:

Your real-time location and emergency alerts are shared with contacts YOU designate
You control who receives what information and can revoke access anytime

Organizational Accounts:

If your employer provides Safeguard, authorized personnel may access your location and safety status during work hours or when you activate emergency features

3.2 Emergency Services

When you activate emergency features, we may share your location and relevant information with 911, police, fire, or medical services
This sharing occurs only during active emergencies or with your explicit consent

3.3 Service Providers
We work with trusted third-party companies that help us operate Safeguard:

Cloud hosting providers (for secure data storage)
Mapping and location services
Analytics platforms (using anonymized data)
Payment processors
Customer support tools
Push notification services

All service providers:

Are contractually required to protect your data
Can only use your information to provide services to us
Cannot sell or share your data for their own purposes

3.4 Legal Requirements
We may disclose your information if required by law:

In response to valid court orders, subpoenas, or legal processes
To comply with law enforcement requests
To protect against legal liability
To prevent imminent harm to individuals or property
To investigate violations of our Terms of Service



4. Data Storage and Security

4.1 Security Measures
We implement industry-leading security practices:

End-to-end encryption for data transmission
AES-256 encryption for data at rest
Secure cloud infrastructure with regular security audits
Multi-factor authentication options for account access
Regular security assessments and penetration testing
Employee training on data protection and privacy
Access controls limiting who can view your data

4.2 Data Storage Locations

Primary servers located in [specify region/country based on compliance]
Backup servers in geographically distributed data centers
All locations comply with international data protection standards

4.3 Data Retention
Active Account Data:

Location data: 90 days (unless part of saved incident reports)
Incident reports: Retained until you delete them
Account information: Until you close your account
Usage analytics: 24 months

After Account Deletion:

Most personal data deleted within 30 days
Some data retained for legal compliance (anonymized after 90 days)
Incident reports saved for safety research (fully anonymized)

You can request complete data deletion at any time by contacting teamnicademiang@gmail.com


5. Location Control
You control when we access your location:

Always Allow: Enables all safety features including background monitoring
While Using App: Provides emergency features but limits background tracking
Never: Disables location features (emergency alerts won't include location)

You can change these settings anytime in your device settings or app preferences.

5.1 Emergency Contact Management

Add or remove emergency contacts at any time
Control what information each contact receives
Temporarily disable contact notifications
View when contacts access your location


6. Children's Privacy
Safeguard is not intended for children under 13 years old without parental consent. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
For Users Aged 13-17:

Parental consent required during account setup
Parents/guardians can access and manage the minor's account
Limited data collection appropriate for minors

If we discover we've collected data from a child under 13 without proper consent, we will delete it immediately.


7. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We use:

Essential Cookies: Required for app functionality (cannot be disabled)
Analytics Cookies: Help us understand how you use the app (can opt out)
Preference Cookies: Remember your settings

Third-Party Tracking:

We do not allow third-party advertising cookies
Analytics partners use anonymized data only
You can manage cookie preferences in app settings


8. Third-Party Links and Services
Safeguard may contain links to external websites or integrate with third-party services (e.g., mapping providers, payment processors).
We are not responsible for:

Privacy practices of third-party websites
Data collection by linked services
Security of external platforms

We recommend reviewing privacy policies of any third-party services you use.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect:

Changes in our practices
New features or services
Legal or regulatory requirements

We will notify you of significant changes via:

In-app notification
Email to your registered address
Prominent notice on our website

Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance. If you disagree with changes, you may delete your account.


10. Your Responsibilities
To protect your account:

Keep your password secure and confidential
Use strong, unique passwords
Enable two-factor authentication
Don't share your account with others
Log out on shared devices
Report suspicious activity immediately


Your Trust Matters
At Safeguard, we understand that trust is essential for a safety app. We are committed to:

Transparency in our data practices
Giving you control over your information
Protecting your data with the highest security standards
Using your information only to keep you safe
Never selling your personal data to third parties

Your safety is our mission. Your privacy is our responsibility.
